value.excerpt: It is "deeply insulting" to describe the Trump administration's border and immigration policies as inhumane, former White House senior adviser Stephen Miller told "Special Report" Monday.

value.title: Biden’s energy policy ‘sends a very dangerous message’ to Texas: George P. Bush
value.excerpt: Texas Land Commissioner George P. Bush, son of Jeb, revealed in an interview with "Fox & Friends" host Brian Kilmeade that he is "taking a very serious look" at running for attorney general and said he should be making his final decision "fairly soon."

value.title: Former Cheney adviser: Biden admin 'hell-bent' on rejoining Iran nuclear deal
value.excerpt: The former National Security Advisor to Vice President Cheney, John Hannah, said that the Biden administration is 'hell-bent' on rejoining the Iran nuclear deal, during a Monday appearance on 'America's Newsroom.'

value.title: Trump, Melania met with cheers at Easter church service in Florida
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump and former First Lady Melania Trump spent their Easter in Florida, attending church before spending time with family at an Easter egg roll at their Mar-a-Lago estate.

value.title: GOP seeks to pull back curtain on Biden tax shelter ‘hypocrisy’
value.excerpt: A blistering letter from the leader of a House conservative caucus regarding Biden’s own tax loopholes could foreshadow what Republicans aim to include in their oversight agenda should they flip the House of Representative in 2022.

value.title: Biden in Easter message calls getting vaccine a 'moral obligation'
value.excerpt: President Biden and First Lady Jill Biden released an Easter video Sunday in which the president insisted that Americans get vaccinated against COVID-19, calling it a "moral obligation."

value.title: Hunter Biden convinced 'reluctant' Joe to publicly support his relationship with Beau's widow Hallie
value.excerpt: Hunter Biden convinced his father Joe in early 2017 to put out a statement approving of the affair he was having with his deceased brother Beau's widow, Hallie Biden, telling Joe that if he didn't, the relationship would "seem wrong."

value.title: Trump campaign and allies refund $122M to WinRed donors: report
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign and allies including the Republican National Committee refunded more than $120 million to online donors in 2020.

value.title: Biden economic adviser says she supports corporate tax increases because it's the 'right thing to do'
value.excerpt: President Biden's economic adviser Cecilia Rouse on Sunday said the president proposes corporate tax increases because it's the "right thing to do."

value.title: Blunt: Biden 'infrastructure' bill should be 30% of current level, slams partisan add-ons as 'big mistake'
value.excerpt: President Biden's massive spending plan needs to be cut by around 70% for Republicans to get on board, Sen. Roy Blunt, R-Mo., suggested on "Fox News Sunday."

value.title: Biden adviser Brian Deese tells 'Fox News Sunday' economy still has 'long way to go,' needs new spending plan
value.excerpt: National Economic Council Director Brian Deese said Sunday that President Biden's new spending plan is still sorely needed despite a strong March jobs report and a variety of other positive economic signs in recent months.

value.title: Biden holds first call with Ukrainian president amid Russian 'aggression' in the region
value.excerpt: President Biden spoke with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky on Friday in their first conversation since Biden took office.

value.title: Trump says companies playing to 'woke cancel culture' over Ga. election bill, calls for boycott
value.excerpt: Former President Trump suggested Saturday that Republicans take a page out of what he sees as Democrats' playbook by boycotting the major businesses that have condemned Georgia's new election reform.

value.title: Biden's quest to pass a multitrillion-dollar spending bill could be imperiled by 'legislative fatigue'
value.excerpt: President Biden and Congressional Democrats are prepping trillions of dollars in new spending.

value.title: Biden reverses Trump, lifts sanctions on International Criminal Court
value.excerpt: President Biden on Friday reversed Trump-era foreign policies by lifting sanctions and removing visa restrictions on officials of the International Criminal Court (ICC).

value.title: Hunter Biden says in memoir he wouldn’t take Burisma job again but insists it wasn’t ‘unethical’
value.excerpt: Hunter Biden wrote in his new tell-all memoir “Beautiful Things” that he does not regret taking a seat on the board of Burisma Holdings, but he would not do it again.

value.title: Tom Homan slams 'outright lies' by Biden, DHS secretary about Border Patrol agents
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor and former acting ICE director Tom Homan told "America's Newsroom" Friday that Border Patrol agents "deserve better" treatment than what the Biden administration is doing for them during the migrant surge at the southern border.

value.title: Gingrich: Biden lied about Georgia election law and he owes the people an apology
value.excerpt: Former Speaker of the House Newt Gingrich joined Bill Hemmer on "America's Newsroom" on Friday to discuss the H.R. 1 election reform bill, accusing President Biden of "flatly false" statements about a new Georgia voting law.

value.title: Abbott claims Biden admin 'clearly in violation' of federal law by overcrowding migrant facilities
value.excerpt: Texas Republican Gov. Greg Abbott called out the Biden administration on "Hannity" Thursday over what Abbott described as "outrageous" conditions in migrant holding facilities near the southern border.

value.title: Sean Hannity: Biden administration waging ‘all-out assault’ on American principles
value.excerpt: President Biden and the Democrats are attempting to destroy American values, "Hannity" host Sean Hannity said.

value.title: Pompeo regrets Trump administration ‘didn’t make more progress’ with North Korea
value.excerpt: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said his “regret” under the Trump administration was not convincing North Korea to give up its nuclear program.

value.title: Former Sen. Perdue slams Biden spending bill as a 'climate change bill at its roots'
value.excerpt: Former Georgia Senator David Perdue slammed President Biden's $2 trillion infrastructure spending bill Thursday, saying it was "a climate change bill at its roots."

value.title: Border crisis result of Biden decisions, 'never seen it close to this bad': Cruz
value.excerpt: Sen. Ted Cruz, R-Texas, argued on "America Reports" Thursday that President Biden "caused the border crisis we are seeing right now" through his immigration actions during his first week in office.

value.title: Biden HHS ad campaign mirrors Dem super PAC ads
value.excerpt: While it is normal for ad blitzes promoting legislation to happen, the ads coincided with a polling memo put out by Priorities USA after the release of the initial ads saying that voters needed to witness Democrats “deliver on policies that provide real benefits to their lives.”
